#
# += For any type of mask, appropriate use and disposal are essential to ensure that they are as effective as possible and to avoid any increase in transmission.
#
#
# += WHO offers the following guidance on the correct use of masks, derived from best practices in health care settings:  perform hand hygiene before putting on the mask; place the mask carefully, ensuring it covers the mouth and nose, adjust to the nose bridge, and tie it securely to minimize any gaps between the face and the mask; avoid touching the mask while wearing it; remove the mask using the appropriate technique: do not touch the front of the mask but untie it from behind.
